<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-577-820  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 577 820.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  August 14 1989 n551 p22(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Senate confirms Bush science adviser: Allan Bromley faces myriadof issues.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Senate confirms President Bush nominee Allan Bromley asdirector of the White House Office of Science and TechnologyPolicy Aug 3, 1989.andP;  Bromley is the Henry Ford II professor ofphysics at Yale Univ and one of the world's preeminent nuclearscientists.andP;  He will provide leadership and input to the Presidenton a wide range of science and technology issues, including: theerosion of the US technology base, joint efforts with theUndersecretary of Commerce for Technology in support of Randamp;D,science and technology budgets, and such major projects ashigh-definition television (HDTV) and the forthcoming US spacestation.andP;  President Bush has made the position an assistant to thePresident with direct access to his office.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Office of Science and Technology PolicyNew AppointmentGoals and ObjectivesRequirements AnalysisScientistsAdministrationExecutive.andO;Person:    Bromley, D. Allan (selection and appointment).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>